{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011M5ySEti3U442Rpg2DHExZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n2\t\n3\tTypeScript package for managing Kanban boards stored as Markdown files with frontmatter and column folders.\n4\t\n5\t## Install\n6\t\n7\t```sh\n8\tnpm install @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n9\t```\n10\t\n11\t## Board Layout\n12\t\n13\t```txt\n14\tboard/\n15\t  todo/\n16\t    fix-login.md\n17\t  doing/\n18\t  done/\n19\t```\n20\t\n21\tEach card is a `.md` file:\n22\t\n23\t```md\n24\t---\n25\ttitle: Fix login\n26\ttags:\n27\t  - bug\n28\torder: 1\n29\tpriority: high\n30\t---\n31\t\n32\tMarkdown body.\n33\t```\n34\t\n35\t## Usage\n36\t\n37\t```ts\n38\timport { Kanbamd } from \"@alejandrocantero/kanbamd\";\n39\t\n40\ttype ProjectFields = {\n41\t  priority?: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\";\n42\t};\n43\t\n44\tconst board = new Kanbamd<ProjectFields>({\n45\t  root: \"./board\",\n46\t  columns: [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"],\n47\t  createRoot: false,\n48\t  createColumns: true\n49\t});\n50\t\n51\tawait board.init();\n52\t\n53\tconst card = await board.createCard(\"todo\", {\n54\t  title: \"Fix login\",\n55\t  tags: [\"bug\"],\n56\t  body: \"OAuth callback fails.\",\n57\t  frontmatter: {\n58\t    priority: \"high\"\n59\t  }\n60\t});\n61\t\n62\tawait board.moveCard(\n63\t  { column: \"todo\", id: card.id },\n64\t  { column: \"doing\" }\n65\t);\n66\t\n67\tawait board.reorderCard({ column: \"doing\", id: card.id }, 0);\n68\t\n69\tconst results = await board.searchCards({\n70\t  query: \"logn callback\",\n71\t  tags: [\"bug\"]\n72\t});\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\t## Memory Storage\n76\t\n77\t```ts\n78\tconst board = new Kanbamd({\n79\t  storage: \"memory\",\n80\t  columns: [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n81\t});\n82\t\n83\tawait board.init();\n84\t```\n85\t\n86\t## Reserved Frontmatter\n87\t\n88\tThese fields are managed by Kanbamd and cannot be provided through custom frontmatter:\n89\t\n90\t- `title`\n91\t- `tags`\n92\t- `order`\n93\t\n94\tFilesystem metadata is exposed as `createdAt` and `updatedAt`.\n95\t\n96\t## CLI\n97\t\n98\tThe package ships with a `kanbamd` command-line interface.\n99\t\n100\t### Global install\n101\t\n102\t```sh\n103\tnpm install -g @alejandrocantero/kanbamd\n104\t```\n105\t\n106\t### Quick start\n107\t\n108\t```sh\n109\t# Create a board with three columns in the current directory\n110\tkanbamd init --columns todo,doing,done\n111\t\n112\t# List columns and their card counts\n113\tkanbamd columns\n114\t\n115\t# Add a card interactively (prompts for column, title, body, tags, order)\n116\tkanbamd add\n117\t\n118\t# List all cards\n119\tkanbamd list\n120\t\n121\t# List cards in a specific column\n122\tkanbamd list --column todo\n123\t\n124\t# View a card (interactive picker if no ID is given)\n125\tkanbamd view\n126\tkanbamd view my-card-slug --column todo\n127\t\n128\t# Move a card to another column (interactive)\n129\tkanbamd move\n130\t\n131\t# Delete a card (interactive, with confirmation)\n132\tkanbamd delete\n133\t\n134\t# Fuzzy-search cards\n135\tkanbamd search \"login bug\"\n136\tkanbamd search \"auth\" --column todo,doing --tags bug --limit 5\n137\t```\n138\t\n139\t### Board config\n140\t\n141\t`kanbamd init` writes a `.kanbamd.json` file to the current directory:\n142\t\n143\t```json\n144\t{\n145\t  \"root\": \".\",\n146\t  \"columns\": [\"todo\", \"doing\", \"done\"]\n147\t}\n148\t```\n149\t\n150\tAll commands look for this file by walking up the directory tree. You can also override root and columns ad-hoc:\n151\t\n152\t```sh\n153\tkanbamd --root ./board --columns todo,doing,done list\n154\t```\n155\t\n156\t### Command reference\n157\t\n158\t| Command | Description |\n159\t|---|---|\n160\t| `init [--root <path>] [--columns <cols>]` | Initialize a board and write `.kanbamd.json` |\n161\t| `columns` | List columns with card counts |\n162\t| `list [-c <col>]` | List all cards, optionally filtered by column |\n163\t| `add` | Interactively create a card (title, body, tags, order) |\n164\t| `view [id] [-c <col>]` | Show card details; launches picker if ID omitted |\n165\t| `move [id] [-c <col>] [--to <col>]` | Move a card to another column |\n166\t| `delete [id] [-c <col>]` | Delete a card with confirmation |\n167\t| `search <query> [-c <cols>] [-t <tags>] [-l <n>]` | Fuzzy-search cards |\n168\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XczoMQ5QRhXmt12Gb2jsAQ","session_id":"7e10c329-12dd-4922-8869-d58b7dccb0a3","uuid":"a311183f-3a2d-4414-9af1-143699a9f7f6","timestamp":"2026-05-03T16:56:21.940Z"}
